{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2b47afc9-83c7-45ab-a2e3-6a0358260460","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n**In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference (`Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`)\n2. **Remove** the separate `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package reference\n3. **Add** the single MSTest v3 package — it bundles the framework, adapter, and test SDK:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n```\n\n**In `OrderServiceTests.cs`:** No changes needed — your `using`, attributes (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`), and `Assert` calls are all compatible with MSTest v3.\n\nYour `net462` target framework is also supported. Want me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b5c7cb64-87b8-4a46-a648-bd0ddd5ce605","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to upgrade from the old MSTest (assembly reference) to MSTest v3. Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove the old assembly reference** to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add the MSTest v3 NuGet package** - MSTest v3 consolidated everything into a single `MSTest` package\n3. **Update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** - or it might be bundled now\n4. **Target framework** - MSTest v3 requires at least .NET Framework 4.6.2, which they already have (net462)\n\n\n5. The namespace stays the same, but the key difference is that MSTest v3's single meta-package bundles the test framework and adapter together, so they just need to add that one package reference and can likely remove the separate SDK package if it was there before. The `using` statements and test code don't need any modifications, so I can now put together a clear summary of the changes required.","outputTokens":731},"id":"9a56f699-5d48-4c9b-a003-73f70c1a21a7","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:55:51.982Z","parentId":"b4fe214d-74c1-4cb0-bb66-6f1235d9045c"}
